DECEMBER 31, 2014

DECREASED FROM DECEMBER 31, 2013 PRIMARILY DUE TO RECLASSIFICATIONS TO CONTRACTUAL BACKLOG RELATED TO INCREMENTAL FUNDING FOR BDS CONTRACTS, PARTIALLY OFFSET BY CONTRACT AWARDS. THE UNOBLIGATED BACKLOG INCREASED DURING 2013 COMPARED TO 2012 PRIMARILY DUE TO CH-47 CHINOOK AND V-22 OSPREY MULTI-YEAR CONTRACT AWARDS. THE INCREASE WAS PARTIALLY OFFSET BY RECLASSIFICATIONS TO CONTRACTUAL BACKLOG RELATED TO INCREMENTAL FUNDING FOR THE U.S. AIR FORCE

KC-46A TANKER

AND F-15 MULTI-YEAR CONTRACTS.

ADDITIONAL CONSIDERATIONS

