. THE INCREASE IN EARNINGS IS PRIMARILY DUE TO HIGHER EARNINGS OF $947 MILLION DRIVEN BY HIGHER NEW AIRPLANE DELIVERIES AND COMMERCIAL AVIATION SERVICES REVENUE GROWTH. THIS EARNINGS INCREASE WAS PARTIALLY OFFSET BY A REACH-FORWARD LOSS OF $238 MILLION RECORDED IN THE SECOND QUARTER OF 2014 RELATED TO THE

USAF KC-46A TANKER

